quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  43,11,"And Who sent down water from the sky with a proper measure, so We revived a dead city with it; this is how you will be taken out."
  43,12,"And the One Who created all pairs, and made the ships and cattle as rides for you."
  43,13,"So that you may properly mount their backs, and may remember your Lord’s favour when you have mounted them, and say, “Purity is to Him, Who has given this ride in our control, and we did not have the strength for it.”"
  43,14,"“And indeed we have to return to our Lord.”"
  43,15,"And from* His bondmen, they appointed a portion for Him; man is indeed an open ingrate. (* Appointed some of His creation as His sons and daughters)."
  43,16,"Has He chosen daughters for Himself from His creation, and selected only sons for you?"
  43,17,"And if one of them is given the glad tidings of what he professes regarding the Most Gracious, his face blackens and he is mournful!"
  43,18,"And (do they chose for Him) one who is brought up among ornaments, and cannot express herself clearly in debate?"
  43,19,"And they appoint the angels, who are the bondmen of the Most Gracious, as females; were they present at the time of the angels’ creation? Their declaration will be now recorded and they will be questioned."
  43,20,"And they say, “If the Most Gracious had willed, we would not have worshipped them!” They do not know its truth at all; they only make guesses."
  43,21,"Or have We given them some Book before this, to which they hold fast?"
  43,22,"Rather they said, “We found our forefathers upon a religion, and we are following their footsteps.”"
